% SimulatorToolbox:SimReadWrite%% Image read and write routines.  Implements the key image data structures.%%   SimCalToMonitor             - Convert psychtoolbox cal file to sim monitor format%   SimCheckRequiredFields      - Check a struct for required fields%   SimEqualCamera              - Are two camera structs equal?%   SimEqualImage               - Are two image structs equal?%   SimEqualMonitor             - Are two monitor structs equal?%   SimFastReadRawImage         - MEX file for fast reading of large image data.%   SimeGetImagePath            - Get path out of full filename%   SimGetl                     - Get a line from an image file, discard comment lines%   SimGrayToMosaic             - Convert mosaiced image from camera to one we can use%   SimImageStringToNumbers     - Convert stings in image structure to numbers.%   SimInitializeImage          - Initialize image structure with blanks.%   SimOneDown                  - Convert first letter of string to lowercase.%   SimOneUp                    - Convert first letter of string to uppercase.%   SimReadCamera               - Read a camera description.%   SimReadCustom               - Read custom fields of a simulator file.%   SimReadCustomField          - Read one custom field of a simulator file.%   SimReadImage                - General image reader.%   SimReadHyperspectralData    - Read hyperspectral data in from disk.%   SimReadMonitor              - Read monitor description.%   SimReadRawImage             - Read raw integer image data.%   SimScale                    - Perform affine scaling to put image data in range [0-1].%   SimTIFFToImage              - Make an image file from a TIFF file.%   SimUnScale                  - Undo affine scaling.%   SimWriteCamera              - Write a camera structure.%   SimWriteCustomField         - Write one field of simulator image.%   SimWriteImage               - Write an image.%   SimWriteMonitor             - Write a monitor file.%   SimWriteRawImage            - Write a raw image.% Copyright (c) 1998, 1999 David Brainard & Philippe Longere. All rights reserved.